@page "/product/companion"
<SeoHead Title="Mobile Companion" Description="A lightweight LifeOS companion for capture, glance, review, outbox and send-to-desktop." CanonicalPath="/product/companion" />
<PageIntro Eyebrow="Product · Mobile Companion" Title="Lightweight by design." Summary="The Companion supports capture, glance, review, outbox and send-to-desktop without pretending to be the full Desktop or future full Mobile app."><StatusBadge Text="v0.1.0-beta.1 complete" Kind="success" /></PageIntro>
<section class="page-shell section"><div class="feature-grid"><article><h2>Capture quickly</h2><p>Record useful state without pulling the whole operating environment onto a phone.</p></article><article><h2>Glance safely</h2><p>Review bounded, mobile-appropriate information instead of a compressed Desktop interface.</p></article><article><h2>Manage the outbox</h2><p>Keep pending sends visible and avoid silent submission loss.</p></article><article><h2>Send to Desktop</h2><p>Move captured state toward the full operating environment for deeper review.</p></article></div></section><section class="page-shell section"><SafetyCallout Label="Product boundary" Title="Companion is not Full Mobile." Text="They may share contracts, identity and design language, but they remain separate applications with distinct purposes, scopes and release tracks." /></section>
